messages.content:
{
  "message": {
    "short_answer": "If the airline cancels your flight HAT216 (CLT → BOS), you are protected even without travel insurance: you are entitled to either a free rebooking or a refund of the unused portion of your ticket.",
    "step_by_step_explanation": {
      "1_if_the_airline_cancels_before_you_travel": {
        "what_the_airline_must_offer": [
          "A) REBOOKING: You can be rebooked on another available flight from CLT to BOS, in **business class**, without paying extra fare (subject to seat availability).",
          "B) REFUND: If you prefer not to travel anymore because of the cancellation, you can request a **refund of the unused portion** of your ticket back to your original payment method (your Mastercard ending in 2734)."
        ],
        "what_you_do_not_have_to_pay": [
          "No change fee for the rebooking caused by the airline’s cancellation.",
          "No additional fare difference if you are rebooked on a comparable flight/itinerary in the same cabin for the same route (as per standard disruption handling)."
        ]
      },
      "2_how_the_process_normally_works": {
        "scenario_a_airline_cancels_in_advance_days_or_hours_before": {
          "likely_flow": [
            "1. You receive a message (email/app/SMS) that HAT216 is cancelled.",
            "2. The system may auto‑offer alternative flights CLT → BOS (same day or next closest).",
            "3. You choose one of the proposed options **or** decline them and request a refund instead.",
            "4. If you choose a refund, the money is returned to your original payment method within about **5–7 business days**."
          ]
        },
        "scenario_b_same_day_cancellation": {
          "likely_flow": [
            "1. At the airport or shortly before departure, the flight shows as cancelled.",
            "2. You are typically rebooked on the next available flight(s) in business or given options to adjust your routing.",
            "3. If those options no longer work for you (for example, it becomes pointless for you to travel), you can request a refund instead of taking the rebooked flight."
          ]
        }
      },
      "3_what_you_are_entitled_to_without_insurance": {
        "you_are_covered_for": [
          "Full refund of the **unused portion** of your ticket if the airline cancels and you choose not to travel.",
          "Rebooking at no extra fare for the same route and cabin, subject to availability.",
          "This protection exists regardless of insurance because the cancellation is initiated by the **airline**, not by you."
        ],
        "difference_if_you_had_insurance": "Insurance mainly helps when *you* cancel for health/weather reasons affecting you personally. For airline‑initiated cancellations, your current rights to rebooking or refund are already strong, even without insurance."
      },
      "4_your_specific_situation_recap": {
        "reservation": "GAST7Q",
        "flight": "HAT216 on 2024-05-21, CLT → BOS",
        "cabin": "business",
        "membership": "silver",
        "practical_effect_for_you": [
          "You are not at risk of “losing all your money” if the airline cancels the flight.",
          "In a cancellation, you will be able to either get where you’re going via rebooking or get your money back for the unused portion."
        ]
      }
    },
    "reassurance": "For your main worry—*the airline cancelling the flight*—you are already meaningfully protected: you will not be forced to absorb the cost if we cancel HAT216. You will have the choice between rebooking and a refund.",
    "question_for_you": "Would you like me to focus next on (a) what happens if there is a long delay rather than a full cancellation, or (b) what to do step‑by‑step if you see a cancellation notice for HAT216 (so you know exactly what to click/ask for)?"
  }
}

